    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-06-29T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-06-29T17:00:00-05:00" n="491"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d491">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">550.S1 Monetary Stabilization/64: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        President <persName type="to">Roosevelt</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-06-29T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 29, 1933—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>29. From Acheson. Your message of June 27 [<hi rend="italic">28?</hi>]<note
                        n="89" xml:id="d491fn89">Telegram No. 15, June 28, 7 p.m., from President
                        Roosevelt, <ref target="#pg_660">p. 660</ref>.</note> containing proposed
                    cable to Delegation has been discussed by Phillips, Baruch and me. In the
                    meantime messages have come from Sprague and Moley stating that they are working
                    on proposal which is in accord with your policy as stated in your cables to
                    Delegation of June 17 and June 20 and which will be cabled tomorrow for
                    submission to you.</p>
                <p>In view of these messages it seemed best to us to withhold your proposed cable to
                    the Delegation and await message from Sprague and Moley. [Acheson.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
